<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-14T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-14T20:00:00-05:00" n="466" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Sonora/699: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Chihuahua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Myers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-14T19:00:00-06:00">April 14, 1929—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 16—4:20 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>General Almazan troop and passenger trains left last night for Ciudad
                            Juarez. The state treasurer published notices today in local papers
                            declaring void all taxes paid from March 3rd to date and demanding that
                            such be paid again immediately.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Myers</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>